### =========================================================================
### Environment Configuration
### =========================================================================
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@contentType = application/json
@deviceId = dev_mock_macbook_pro_99
@appVersion = 1.4.2

### =========================================================================
### 1. Warmup Infrastructure (GET)
### =========================================================================
# Kicks off Next.js Lambda, Pings Redis, and provisions Firestore client pool
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/warm-up
User-Agent: LocalRESTClient/1.0
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### =========================================================================
### 2. Request / Resend OTP via Email (POST)
### =========================================================================
# @name resendEmailOtp
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/warm-up
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_15_7)

{
    "identity": "developer@example.com",
    "channel": "email",
    "deviceId": "{{deviceId}}",
    "appVersion": "{{appVersion}}"
}

###

### =========================================================================
### 3. Request / Resend OTP via SMS (POST)
### =========================================================================
# @name resendSmsOtp
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/warm-up
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (iPhone; CPU iPhone OS 17_0 like Mac OS X)

{
    "identity": "+15555550199",
    "channel": "phone",
    "deviceId": "{{deviceId}}",
    "appVersion": "{{appVersion}}"
}

###

### =========================================================================
### 4. Malformed Request Test (Validation Error Catch)
### =========================================================================
# Sends missing device ID and incorrect channel enum to test Zod validation
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/warm-up
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
    "identity": "+15555550199",
    "channel": "carrier-pigeon",
    "deviceId": "",
    "appVersion": "1.0.0"
}